\viewkind4\uc1\pard\keepn\s5\lang2057\ul\b\f0\fs24 FTDI Win 2k Drivers - Revision Comments  February 4, 2004\ulnone\par
\pard\keepn\s6\ul\b0\fs16 C:\\WINDOWS\\Desktop\\Releases\\Drivers\\Beta Release 905 2151 Feb04,2004\\2151 Release Info.doc\par
\pard\ulnone\fs20\par
FTDI\rquote s drivers have been changed to accommodate the support of Windows 98 and Windows 2000 for all three of FTDI\rquote s USB controllers from a single INF file. \par
\par
New drivers will be posted on the support page of FTDI\rquote s web page - in ZIP format, following the following naming convention - Rxxyy where xx is the version of the Windows 98 drivers and yy is the version of the Windows 2000 drivers. The first release of the common INF drivers was named R0855.zip - which is version 10208 of the Windows 98 drivers and version 2055 of the Windows 2000 drivers.\par
\par
There are now six files which are provided as a standard release\par
\par
FTDIBUS.SYS (two driver files)\par
FTSER2K.SYS\par
FTDIUNIN.EXE (uninstaller and associated ini file)\par
FTDIUN2K.INI\par
FTDIBUS.INF (two shared INF files for Win98 and Win2k)\par
FTDIPORT.INF \par
\par
On making a new release the files will also be posted onto FTDI\rquote s web page \cf1\ul http://www.ftdichip.com\cf0\ulnone .\par
Proceed to the support page to download drivers (select Support tab at top of screen).\par
\par
